## Notes

- Direct insertion into agent_triggers was rejected by Supabase RLS, so the self-test used the normal messages insertion path, which creates agent_triggers through the production DB path.
- One post-cooldown attempt through scripts/run-native-pentagon-task.mjs failed because that harness read an expired JWT before Pentagon refreshed the preference plist. The successful post-cooldown proof used a fresh Supabase session for the message insert and did not require production-code changes.
- The bridge was SIGSTOP/SIGCONT controlled during the test to preserve in-memory cooldown state and prevent normal relay work from claiming synthetic triggers before they crossed the 60 second stuck threshold.
